Metadata: Diterpenes from the brown alga "Dictyota bartayresiana."

"Dictyota" species of the Indian Ocean continue to be good sources of novel structural types of diterpenes. The alga "Dictyota bartayresiana" Lamaroux (Phaeophyceae) remained a target of chemical analysis for secondary metabolites. A specimen collected from Hare Island in the Gulf of Mannar yielded five known and three new dolabellanes, and one known and two new dolastanes.
